        output='Based on the provided MD&A and Preamble excerpts, the company discloses a comprehensive set of quantitative metrics for its **Connectivity segment** (primarily driven by Starlink). \n\nHere is the detailed breakdown of the disclosed metrics, categorized by subscribers, ARPU, terminal/kit deployments, network performance, and financial indicators.\n\n### 1. Subscriber & User Base Metrics\nThe company tracks its user base through "Starlink Subscribers" (defined as unique Service Lines directly assigned to an account) and mobile device connections.\n*   **Starlink Subscribers (in millions):**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** 10.3 million *(104.7% YoY growth)*\n    *   **Q1 2025:** 5.0 million\n    *   **FY 2025:** 8.9 million *(99.9% YoY growth)*\n    *   **FY 2024:** 4.4 million *(96.5% YoY growth)*\n    *   **FY 2023:** 2.3 million\n*   **Mobile Connectivity:** ~7.4 million monthly unique devices using satellite-to-mobile texting and over-the-top voice services across ~30 countries.\n*   **Geographic Reach:** Service available across 164 countries, territories, and markets, covering a total addressable population of more than 3.3 billion people.\n\n### 2. ARPU (Average Revenue Per User)\nStarlink Subscriber ARPU is tracked monthly. The company notes a steady decline in ARPU, which it explicitly attributes to international expansion (entering lower-income markets) and the introduction of lower-priced service plans.\n*   **Q1 2026:** $66 / month *(22.9% YoY decline)*\n*   **Q1 2025:** $86 / month\n*   **FY 2025:** $81 / month *(11.2% YoY decline)*\n*   **FY 2024:** $91 / month *(8.1% YoY decline)*\n*   **FY 2023:** $99 / month\n\n### 3. Terminal Deployments & Hardware Metrics\nWhile the company **does not disclose an exact unit count** of deployed physical terminals, it tracks terminal deployments quantitatively through financial spend on "Starlink Kits" and its definition of "Service Lines":\n*   **Service Lines as a Proxy:** A "Service Line" is generally associated with a specific Starlink terminal or group of terminals. Therefore, the **10.3 million Starlink Subscribers** metric serves as the primary proxy for active terminal deployments.\n*   **Starlink Kit Financial Volume (Cost of Revenue):** In FY 2024, the company disclosed a **$907 million** higher volume spend on Starlink Kits driven by "higher kit deliveries."\n*   **Starlink Kit R&D:** In Q1 2026, the company disclosed **$8 million** in R&D costs dedicated to next-generation Starlink Kits.\n\n### 4. Network & Broadband Performance Indicators\nThe company discloses specific operational metrics regarding its Low-Earth Orbit (LEO) constellation\'s performance as of March 31, 2026:\n*   **Satellites in Orbit:** ~9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites.\n*   **Median Latency:** ~25 milliseconds.\n*   **Median Download Speeds:** 225 Mbps during peak hours for residential users (described as "fiber-like").\n\n### 5. Revenue Metrics (Disaggregated)\nConnectivity revenue is split between Consumer and Enterprise/Government segments.\n*   **Total Connectivity Revenue:**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $3,257M *(+31.6% YoY)* | Q1 2025: $2,475M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $11,387M *(+49.8% YoY)* | FY 2024: $7,599M | FY 2023: $3,869M\n*   **Consumer Revenue:**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $2,148M | Q1 2025: $1,492M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $7,208M | FY 2024: $4,830M | FY 2023: $2,817M\n*   **Enterprise & Government Revenue:**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $1,109M | Q1 2025: $983M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $4,179M | FY 2024: $2,769M | FY 2023: $1,052M\n    *   *FY 2025 Sub-drivers:* Enterprise connectivity grew by $1,218M (inclusive of $632M from mobile connectivity); Government connectivity grew by $193M.\n\n### 6. Profitability, Cost, & Capital Metrics\n*   **Segment Income from Operations:**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $1,188M | Q1 2025: $1,033M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $4,423M *(+120.4% YoY)* | FY 2024: $2,006M | FY 2023: $469M\n*   **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $2,087M | Q1 2025: $1,618M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $7,168M *(+86.2% YoY)* | FY 2024: $3,849M | FY 2023: $1,602M\n*   **Depreciation & Amortization:** \n    *   **FY 2025:** $2,376M | **FY 2023:** $884M *(Driven by capitalized launch and satellite costs).*\n*   **Capital Expenditures (CapEx):**\n    *   **Q1 2026:** $1,332M\n    *   **FY 2025:** $4,178M\n    *   **FY 2023:** $2,455M\n*   **Cost of Revenue Drivers (Q1 2026):** Increased by $437M YoY, heavily driven by $276M in higher satellite/launch depreciation and $140M in ground operating costs ($50M), customer support/installation ($42M), payment processor fees ($19M), freight ($15M), and warranty ($12M).',
