antifies the *increases/decreases* for three specific sub-buckets:\n1.  **Aviation, maritime, and other enterprise business** (e.g., increased by $209 million in Q1 2026).\n2.  **Mobile connectivity business** (e.g., increased by $85 million in Q1 2026; noted as a $632 million subset of enterprise growth in full-year 2025).\n3.  **Government connectivity business** (e.g., decreased by $175 million in Q1 2026; Starshield is implicitly housed here but not quantified on its own). \n\n*(Note: The narrative also breaks out Consumer revenue variances by subscriber growth vs. ARPU declines, but this is a metric breakdown rather than a product sub-category).*',
